snippet.textDisplay:
Folk song of Punjab :dialogue between Clay pot(used in old days as floating device to cross the river) Ali   and Sohni(lover) Shilpa Rao . Clay pot is advising her not to cross the river in stormy night and his own unreliability as a reason.She is insisting that she has to cross due to her yearning even if it means her meeting her lover as a corpse. Last part  when the third singer jumps in is giving her encouragement to rely on Divine help with his murshid's guidance.
This is another song that is the metaphor for human longing to unite with his divine lover using worldly knowledge  trying to go through the river of trials and tribulations, the real way to achieve this is through the help of guide (murshid)
